-- China is World's Biggest Market for Commodities Futures, Regulator Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-06T06:18:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-06/china-is-world-s-biggest-market-for-commodities-futures-regulator-says.html
China has become the world’s biggest
market for commodities futures trading, the country’s security
regulator said.  Futures trading volume in China has surged 51 percent from
a year ago while turnover jumped 137 percent, Jiang Yang,
chairman assistant of the China Securities Regulatory Commission,
said at a conference in Guangzhou today, without providing
details.  -- William Bi . Editors: Jim McDonald  To contact the reporter on this story:
